# Windsurf legacy rules — cp_book

> Same content as `.windsurf/rules/cp_book.md`. Kept for older
> Windsurf versions that read the root `.windsurfrules` file.
>
> **Source of truth: `AGENTS.md` at the repo root and the matching
> `.ai/modules/<folder>.md` for whatever folder you're editing.**

## Style rules — match exactly, do not "improve"

- Hard tabs. K&R braces. `snake_case`. `struct` (never `class`).
- CAPS for dimension template params / constants (`N`, `M`, `K`, `MOD`).
- Pass all inputs by `const T&` — including primitives.
- Inherit from STL containers for vector-shaped structures.
- Doc-block opens `/**` and closes `**/` (two stars).
- Keep deliberate spaces inside `++ i`, `-- i`, `~ v`, `- 1`,
  `operator <`.
- Asserts wrapped in `#ifdef _GLIBCXX_DEBUG`.
- Always write `std::`. No `using namespace std;` in headers.
- SFINAE via `typename std::enable_if<…>::type`. No C++20 concepts.
- Headers don't include `<bits/stdc++.h>`; tests include it once.

## Don't

- Don't reformat with `clang-format`.
- Don't touch code you weren't asked to touch.
- Don't introduce `shared_ptr`, `<format>`, coroutines, ranges,
  concepts on hot paths.
- Don't bypass `[!benchmark]`.
- Don't add per-folder meta files inside source folders.

## Do

- Read `.ai/modules/<folder>.md` first.
- Add a regression test alongside any library patch
  (see `library_fixes.md`).
- Mirror source layout when adding tests.
